---
By: Michael A. Sydner
Locus:
  Page: 43
  Verse: 16
Tags:
  - Cause
---
Humanity, it seems, always treats the physical effects, not the spiritual
causes—lust, greed, selfishness. Humanity always ends up treating the
effects—not the cause. To treat the causes would change lifestyles—even
this civilization itself! And that humanity is unwilling to do.
